    {
      "title": "Feminine Demonstrative and Pronoun",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الإشارة والضمير للمؤنث",
      "content": [
        "هَذِهِ (hādhihi) is the feminine equivalent of هَذَا, meaning 'this' for feminine nouns. هِيَ (hiya) means 'she/it' for feminine nouns.",
        "Many feminine nouns end with ة (taa marbuta), which is pronounced as 'a' or 'at' depending on the grammatical context. This ending is a key marker of feminine gender."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "هَذِهِ is 'this' for feminine nouns",
        "هِيَ is 'she/it' for feminine nouns",
        "Most nouns ending in ة (taa marbuta) are feminine",
        "Some family words have distinct feminine forms: أَخٌ (brother) → أُخْتٌ (sister)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "هَذِهِ سَيَّارَةٌ", "english": "This is a car" },
        { "arabic": "هِيَ أُخْتٌ", "english": "She is a sister" },
        { "arabic": "هَذِهِ طَاوِلَةٌ", "english": "This is a table" },
        { "arabic": "مَنْ هِيَ؟ هِيَ أُمٌّ", "english": "Who is she? She is a mother" }
      ]
    }
